The paper discusses the effect of caching on wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed strategy is based on exploiting multi-user diversity gain, which is a concept commonly used in wireless communication systems (cs.SI). The paper also derives a closed-form result for throughput scaling, which involves mathematical analysis and modeling (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between cache memory size and network throughput, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
